LineUp HTMLWidget in R Markdown

This is a simple example how to include the LineUp HTMLWidget in your R Markdown file

library(lineup)

Simple Example

lineup(iris)

Cross Talk

The LineUp HTMLWidget supports Crosstalk to sync selection and filtering among widgets.

devtools::install_github("jcheng5/d3scatter")
## Skipping install of 'd3scatter' from a github remote, the SHA1 (aba6687f) has not changed since last install.
##   Use `force = TRUE` to force installation
library(d3scatter)

shared_iris = SharedData$new(iris)

d3scatter(shared_iris, ~Petal.Length, ~Petal.Width, ~Species, width="100%")
lineup(shared_iris, width="100%")
shared_mtcars = SharedData$new(mtcars)

bscols(widths = c(3,NA),
  list(
    filter_checkbox("cyl", "Cylinders", shared_mtcars, ~cyl, inline = TRUE),
    filter_slider("hp", "Horsepower", shared_mtcars, ~hp, width = "100%")
  ),
  lineup(shared_mtcars, width="100%")
)
